org.urbanbyte.cueserver.http

Class HttpCueServerClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.urbanbyte.cueserver.http.HttpCueServerClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CueServerClient

    public class HttpCueServerClient
extends java.lang.Object
implements CueServerClient
    The CueServerClient facilitates interaction with a CueServer. Clients have the ability to retrieve state related information, and send commands to a CueServer using it HTTP interface.

    author: Chris Reising

      • recordCue

        public void recordCue(double cueNumber,
                      double uptimeSecs,
                      double downtimeSecs)
        Records a cue.
        Specified by:
        recordCue in interface CueServerClient
        Parameters:
        cueNumber - the cue number to record. Must be positive. The CueServer only supports up to one decimal place for cue number (e.g., 10.1). The value passed in will be truncated to accommodate this.
        uptimeSecs - the fade's uptime in seconds. Must be within [0, 65000]. The precision is up to a tenth of a second.
        downtimeSecs - the fade's downtime in seconds. Must be within [0, 65000]. The precision is up to a tenth of a second.
